article.headline: Kent State 67, Northern Illinois 55
article.story: KENT, Ohio (AP) -- DeAndre Haynes scored 24 points to lead Kent State to a 67-55 win over Northern Illinois on Sunday. Mike Scott's dunk with 5:30 remaining capped a 12-4 run for Kent (17-7, 11-2 Mid-American Conference) and gave the Golden Flashes a 56-41 lead. Scott finished with 13 points, and Armon Gates added 11 for Kent, which rebounded from Tuesday's 60-44 loss at Toledo. Cory Sims led Northern Illinois (13-9, 8-6) with 14 points. Zach Pancratz had 13. The Huskies, which have lost two in a row, shot just 46.4 percent from the field (20-of-48). Northern Illinois had shot 50 percent or better in 10 of its 13 victories this season and came in to Sunday's game having totaled a MAC-best field-goal percentage of 48.5 percent.
